2011-10-21T20:23:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-21/kocherlakota-says-fed-shifting-objectives-for-inflation-audio-.html
Federal Reserve Bank of  Minneapolis  
President Narayana Kocherlakota talks about Fed monetary policy 
and measures of inflation.  Kocherlakota, speaking in Minneapolis, says he takes issue 
with what he says are the central bank's shifting objectives for
inflation since last year, saying it weakens policy makers' 
credibility. (Source: Bloomberg)  00:00 Kocherlakota offers opening remarks.
02:24 Federal Reserve system, dual mandate
14:15 FOMC decision making; inflation, unemployment
25:25 FOMC "more tolerant" of inflation risks
30:03 Kocherlakota responds to questions.  Running time 51:22
 